s. It explores cognition, memory, perception, and neurological disorders at molecular, cellular, and systems levels.", "Astrophysics is the branch of astronomy that applies physics principles to understand celestial objects, including stars, galaxies, and black holes. It studies phenomena like gravitational waves, cosmic microwave background radiation, and stellar evolution."], "scores": [0.6849391470694526, 0.47468108935487613, 0.3250744776831283, 0.3062382973647221, 0.3037762422402722], "model_name": "mpnet", "document_ids": ["Robotics", "Cybernetics", "Thermodynamics", "Neuroscience", "Astrophysics"]}}